In this speech, President Donald Trump addresses a gathering of veterans at the Galt House Hotel in Louisville, Kentucky. He expresses his gratitude for their service and discusses his administration's efforts to support veterans. Trump highlights the improvements made in providing medical care for veterans, including the Veterans Choice program, which allows veterans to see private doctors and have the bill paid by the government. He also mentions the VA Accountability Act, which allows for the removal of underperforming employees at the Department of Veterans Affairs. Trump emphasizes the need to address the issue of veteran suicide and announces his intention to eliminate federal student loan debt for permanently disabled veterans. He also discusses the achievements of his administration in reducing veteran unemployment and expanding the GI Bill. The speech concludes with Trump signing a presidential memorandum facilitating the cancellation of student loan debt for severely disabled veterans.